{"terr": "Romania","region": "Europe","certLow": 39,"certHigh": 39,"payLow": 17,"payHigh": 17,"sourceQuality": "industry_secondary","sourceNote": "Stated process: payment request+audit within 9 months (~39wk) of financing agreement, then payment within 120 days (~17wk) of approval \u2014 but REAL HISTORY of severe backlog (~EUR100M owed, \"ground to a halt\", lawsuits, per Variety 2023) before a 2024 relaunch. Culture minister still discussing \"repairing\" confidence as of Cannes 2026. Treat with real-world caution despite the stated process looking reasonable on paper. [CORRECTED 2026-07: schoenherr.eu is a law firm summarizing the regulation, not the Romanian Film Office's own site \u2014 downgraded from government_plus_industry. The BACKLOG HISTORY (Variety, real journalism) remains solid regardless of this correction.]","realWorldConfirms": false,"suspended": false,"sourceUrl": "https://www.schoenherr.eu/content/the-revamped-cash-rebate-system-a-new-promise-for-the-romanian-film-industry","aiNarrativeRule": "IMPORTANT: the STATED process looks reasonable on paper (9 months to submit + 120 days to pay), but REAL-WORLD EVIDENCE CONTRADICTS IT \u2014 a documented history of a severe payment backlog (~EUR100M owed, described by Variety as having 'ground to a halt'), only recently addressed by a 2024 system relaunch that is still being described as 'repairing confidence' as of Cannes 2026. Always pair any mention of Romania's stated timeline with this real backlog history \u2014 never cite the stated process alone as if it reflects actual experience."},
