{"terr": "India","region": "Asia","certLow": null,"certHigh": null,"payLow": null,"payHigh": null,"sourceQuality": "government_direct","sourceNote": "CATEGORIZED (2026-07) as STRUCTURALLY DISCRETIONARY, confirmed -- not an unresearched gap. India's Audio-Visual Co-Production and International Shooting Incentive is processed via committee evaluation (Special Incentive Evaluation Committee, per the Ministry of Information & Broadcasting's own published guidelines), disbursed in two stages (interim, final) with no statutory clock at any stage. This is a REAL FINDING in itself: a committee-discretionary system is inherently less predictable/bankable than a statutory-deadline system, independent of the headline rate. Reflects genuine programme design, not a research shortfall.","realWorldConfirms": null,"suspended": false,"sourceUrl": "https://mib.gov.in/sites/default/files/2024-02/Revised%20incentive%20guidelines.pdf","aiNarrativeRule": "STRUCTURALLY DISCRETIONARY BY DESIGN, confirmed via the Ministry of Information & Broadcasting's own published guidelines: disbursement runs through a Special Incentive Evaluation Committee with no statutory clock at either the interim or final stage. This is a real, deliberate finding, not a missing data point \u2014 cite it as 'discretionary, no fixed timeline by design,' which is itself meaningful bankability information (a discretionary system is inherently less predictable than a statutory one, independent of the headline rate)."},
{"terr": "Japan","region": "Asia","certLow": null,"certHigh": null,"payLow": null,"payHigh": null,"sourceQuality": "government_direct","sourceNote": "CATEGORIZED (2026-07) as STRUCTURALLY DISCRETIONARY, confirmed: Japan's METI/VIPO/JFC-administered incentive is explicitly a discretionary grant-budget model -- the funding amount per production is 'decided by a committee after consideration of the application content and number of applicants' (Deadline/Screen Daily, corroborating METI's own programme description). There is no legally mandated treasury disbursement timeframe by design, not by omission. Same real-finding logic as India: discretionary committee-based systems are inherently less predictable than statutory ones, and that IS the bankability answer, not a placeholder for a missing one. [REJECTED CLAIM 2026-07: an external source claimed Japan 'lacks a centralized national tax credit or cash rebate program.' This is FALSE and directly contradicted by this session's own verified findings (Deadline, Variety, Screen Daily): METI/VIPO/JFC's Location Incentive is real, national, offers a 50% rebate up to JPY1BN (~$6.8M), launched 2023, extended to a multi-year programme Dec 2025, and has funded major productions including Apple TV+'s Monarch and Skydance's Neuromancer. Do not use the external claim. The 'structurally discretionary, no statutory clock' finding already in this record remains the correct, confirmed characterization.","realWorldConfirms": null,"suspended": false,"sourceUrl": "https://deadline.com/2023/09/japan-incentive-program-offshore-production-vipo-meti-1235542659/","aiNarrativeRule": "STRUCTURALLY DISCRETIONARY BY DESIGN, confirmed via trade press describing METI's programme: funding per production is decided by committee evaluation with no legally mandated treasury disbursement timeframe. This is a real, deliberate finding, not a missing data point \u2014 cite it as 'discretionary, no fixed timeline by design.'"}
